Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Sandwich each @British Chicken Breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2 cm thick. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk. Put the @breadcrumbs{50%g} into another medium bowl, then season with the @salt{1/2%tsp} and pepper.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated.

Transfer to a clean #plate{}. > Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @olive oil{} to coat the bottom of the pan. > You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a large #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Discard the oil from the chicken pan.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{} for the pasta.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g} using a #grater{}.

== Cheesy Garlic Ciabatta ==

Halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto a #medium baking tray{}, cut-side up. Spread over the garlic and drizzle with the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the garlic bread. Sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

== Chicken Parmigiana ==

Once the chicken has finished cooking, remove from the oven, spoon over the @marinara sauce{120%g} and top with the grated Cheddar. Return to the middle shelf of your oven until golden and bubbling, ~{4-5%minutes}.

At the same time, transfer the garlic ciabatta to the top shelf and bake until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== Parma Ham and Pesto Pasta ==

While everything's in the oven, add the @parma ham & Parmigiano Reggiano filled pasta{250%g} to your pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{3%minutes}.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and gently transfer back to the pan.

Stir through the @pesto{64%g} and @butter{20%g} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Share your chicken parmigiana and pesto pasta between your plates.

Serve the @baby leaf mix{20%g} and tomatoes alongside and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Serve with the cheesy garlic ciabatta alongside. Enjoy!